{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_07_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 7 - G in the Air",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 9.25,
  "page_end_sec": 258.28,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.735,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 9.25,
      "end": 10.58,
      "text": "CHAPTER VII."
    },
    {
      "start": 10.62,
      "end": 10.88,
      "text": "G."
    },
    {
      "start": 11.8,
      "end": 12.68,
      "text": "IN THE AIR."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.78,
      "end": 16.62,
      "text": "In his bedroom that was a living-room,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 16.72,
      "end": 17.88,
      "text": "now the wall-bed was up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.4,
      "end": 19.83,
      "text": "Spade took Bridget O'Shaughnessy's"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.98,
      "end": 20.6,
      "text": "hat and coat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 20.8,
      "end": 23.16,
      "text": "made her comfortable in a padded rocking-chair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.4,
      "end": 25.0,
      "text": "and after looking up the number"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.16,
      "end": 26.08,
      "text": "in the telephone directory,"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.42,
      "end": 28.1,
      "text": "called the Hotel Belvedere."
    },
    {
      "start": 29.12,
      "end": 30.6,
      "text": "Cairo had not yet returned from the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 30.68,
      "end": 30.9,
      "text": "theater."
    },
    {
      "start": 31.68,
      "end": 34.02,
      "text": "Spade left his telephone number with the request",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 34.02,
      "end": 36.3,
      "text": "that Cairo call him as soon as he came in."
    },
    {
      "start": 38.048,
      "end": 40.3,
      "text": "Spade sat down in the armchair beside the table,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 40.94,
      "end": 42.21,
      "text": "and without any preliminaries,"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.68,
      "end": 44.14,
      "text": "without any introductory remarks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.57,
      "end": 47.56,
      "text": "began to tell the girl about a thing that had happened three"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.62,
      "end": 48.82,
      "text": "years before in the Northwest."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.22,
      "end": 51.26,
      "text": "He talked in a steady,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 51.42,
      "end": 52.62,
      "text": "matter-of-fact tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.05,
      "end": 54.0,
      "text": "devoid of emphasis"
    },
    {
      "start": 54.26,
      "end": 55.0,
      "text": "or pauses,"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.16,
      "end": 59.62,
      "text": "though now and then he repeated a sentence slightly rearranged,"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.72,
      "end": 60.78,
      "text": "as if it were"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.88,
      "end": 64.06,
      "text": "important to relate each detail exactly as it had happened."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.28,
      "end": 65.7,
      "text": "His eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 65.78,
      "end": 66.34,
      "text": "while he talked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.5,
      "end": 68.14,
      "text": "looked at the memories over her shoulder."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.7,
      "end": 71.88,
      "text": "At the beginning she listened with only partial",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 71.98,
      "end": 72.48,
      "text": "attentiveness,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.76,
      "end": 76.52,
      "text": "obviously more surprised by the story than interested in it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.6,
      "end": 78.04,
      "text": "her curiosity more"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.16,
      "end": 79.7,
      "text": "engaged with his purpose in telling"
    },
    {
      "start": 79.7,
      "end": 81.66,
      "text": "the story than with the story he told."
    },
    {
      "start": 82.0,
      "end": 83.42,
      "text": "But presently,"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.66,
      "end": 84.98,
      "text": "as the story went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.44,
      "end": 87.94,
      "text": "it caught her more and more fully and held her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.04,
      "end": 89.58,
      "text": "and she became still"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.8,
      "end": 90.22,
      "text": "and receptive."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.16,
      "end": 94.34,
      "text": "A man named Flitcraft had left his real",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 94.34,
      "end": 96.52,
      "text": "estate office in Tacoma to go to luncheon"
    },
    {
      "start": 96.52,
      "end": 98.14,
      "text": "one day and had never returned."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.84,
      "end": 102.58,
      "text": "He did not keep an engagement to play golf after four that afternoon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.2,
      "end": 105.98,
      "text": "though he had taken the initiative in making the"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.98,
      "end": 108.5,
      "text": "engagement a bare half-hour before he went out to"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.72,
      "end": 108.94,
      "text": "luncheon."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.55,
      "end": 112.0,
      "text": "His wife and children never saw him again."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.12,
      "end": 114.86,
      "text": "His wife and he were supposed to be on",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 114.86,
      "end": 115.7,
      "text": "the best of terms."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.28,
      "end": 117.62,
      "text": "He had two children,"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.82,
      "end": 118.22,
      "text": "boys,"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.54,
      "end": 119.94,
      "text": "one five and one three."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.0,
      "end": 122.51,
      "text": "He owned his home in a Tacoma",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 122.58,
      "end": 123.0,
      "text": "suburb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.48,
      "end": 125.64,
      "text": "a new Packard car already paid for,"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.86,
      "end": 129.0,
      "text": "and the rest of the appurtenances of successful American"
    },
    {
      "start": 129.2,
      "end": 129.48,
      "text": "living."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.232,
      "end": 134.34,
      "text": "Footcraft had inherited seventy thousand dollars from his father,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 134.61,
      "end": 136.1,
      "text": "and with his success in"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.2,
      "end": 136.54,
      "text": "real estate,"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.74,
      "end": 138.44,
      "text": "was worth something in the neighborhood"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.44,
      "end": 140.7,
      "text": "of $200,000 at the time of his"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.76,
      "end": 141.16,
      "text": "vanishing."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.56,
      "end": 143.62,
      "text": "His affairs were in order,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 143.76,
      "end": 146.52,
      "text": "though there were enough loose ends to indicate that he had not"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.58,
      "end": 149.18,
      "text": "been setting his affairs in order preparatory to vanishing."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.07,
      "end": 151.82,
      "text": "A deal that would have brought him an",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 151.86,
      "end": 152.56,
      "text": "attractive profit,"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.78,
      "end": 153.18,
      "text": "for instance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.42,
      "end": 156.34,
      "text": "was to be completed the day after that in which he had"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.4,
      "end": 156.7,
      "text": "vanished."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.18,
      "end": 159.9,
      "text": "There was nothing to show that he had more",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 159.9,
      "end": 161.9,
      "text": "than fifty or sixty dollars in his immediate"
    },
    {
      "start": 162.2,
      "end": 164.0,
      "text": "possession at the time of his going."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.5,
      "end": 168.4,
      "text": "His time for months past could be at least roughly accounted",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 168.66,
      "end": 172.1,
      "text": "for too thoroughly to justify any suspicion of secret vices,"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.32,
      "end": 174.14,
      "text": "or even of another woman,"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.54,
      "end": 176.6,
      "text": "though of course either was possible."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.66,
      "end": 180.36,
      "text": "\"'He went like that,' Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 180.62,
      "end": 183.04,
      "text": "\"'Like a fist when you open your hand.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.54,
      "end": 187.6,
      "text": "When he had reached this point in his story the telephone bell rang.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 188.45,
      "end": 190.68,
      "text": "Hello?\" he said into the instrument.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 191.38,
      "end": 191.56,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 191.68,
      "end": 192.04,
      "text": "Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 192.64,
      "end": 193.2,
      "text": "this is Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 194.08,
      "end": 195.42,
      "text": "Can you come up to my place,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 195.52,
      "end": 195.94,
      "text": "Poe Street,"
    },
    {
      "start": 196.1,
      "end": 196.36,
      "text": "now?"
    },
    {
      "start": 196.92,
      "end": 197.38,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 197.48,
      "end": 198.464,
      "text": "I think it is.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 199.0,
      "end": 200.28,
      "text": "He looked at the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 200.46,
      "end": 201.34,
      "text": "pursed his lips,"
    },
    {
      "start": 201.36,
      "end": 202.36,
      "text": "and then said quickly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.32,
      "end": 205.46,
      "text": "Miss O'Shaughnessy is here and wants to see you.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 206.64,
      "end": 208.78,
      "text": "She frowned a little and stirred in her chair,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 208.88,
      "end": 209.68,
      "text": "but said nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.816,
      "end": 212.64,
      "text": "Spade put down the telephone and told her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 213.7,
      "end": 214.82,
      "text": "He'll be up in a few minutes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 215.46,
      "end": 216.22,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.44,
      "end": 217.98,
      "text": "that was in 1922."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.14,
      "end": 223.76,
      "text": "In 1927 I was with one of the National Detective Agencies in Seattle.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 224.46,
      "end": 225.12,
      "text": "Mrs."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.26,
      "end": 227.9,
      "text": "Flitcraft came in and told us somebody had"
    },
    {
      "start": 227.9,
      "end": 230.32,
      "text": "seen a man who resembled her husband in Spokane."
    },
    {
      "start": 231.76,
      "end": 232.9,
      "text": "I went over there for her.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 233.66,
      "end": 234.48,
      "text": "It was Flitcraft,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 234.62,
      "end": 234.98,
      "text": "all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.0,
      "end": 239.08,
      "text": "He had been living in Spokane for a couple of years as Charles,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 239.24,
      "end": 240.68,
      "text": "that was his first name,"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.84,
      "end": 241.16,
      "text": "Pierce."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.62,
      "end": 244.38,
      "text": "He had an automobile business that was netting"
    },
    {
      "start": 244.38,
      "end": 246.34,
      "text": "him twenty or twenty-five thousand a year,"
    },
    {
      "start": 246.46,
      "end": 247.26,
      "text": "a wife,"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.36,
      "end": 248.04,
      "text": "a baby son,"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.3,
      "end": 250.52,
      "text": "owned his home in a Spokane suburb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 250.98,
      "end": 252.78,
      "text": "had all the trimmings that go with that"
    },
    {
      "start": 252.78,
      "end": 253.52,
      "text": "kind of success,"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.82,
      "end": 256.42,
      "text": "and usually got away to play golf after"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.42,
      "end": 258.28,
      "text": "four in the afternoon during the season."
    }
  ]
}